<Desc><entry>Aims to offer emotional and practical support to those affected by any crime, harassment or anti-social behaviour.  The work is one-to-one with the direct victim and also with their family and friends.  Support is given out in the community and/or at the Magistrates and Crown Courts.  Represents people claiming Criminal Injury Compensation.  Volunteer workers are CRB checked and trained.</entry>
</Desc>
